00:10:24.123 --> 00:10:26.209 align:middle line:84%
see more of this heart
rate variability.

00:10:26.209 --> 00:10:28.336 align:middle line:90%
But here's what happens.

00:10:28.336 --> 00:10:29.712 align:middle line:90%
As we get older--

00:10:29.712 --> 00:10:31.840 align:middle line:84%
and I know you've heard
this term before--

00:10:31.840 --> 00:10:36.636 align:middle line:84%
as we get older, the tendency is
that we become set in our ways.

00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:38.179 align:middle line:84%
Or another way to
think of that is we

00:10:38.179 --> 00:10:41.266 align:middle line:90%
become rigid in our thinking.

00:10:41.266 --> 00:10:44.727 align:middle line:84%
We expect the world to
behave in certain ways.

00:10:44.727 --> 00:10:47.981 align:middle line:84%
We expect people to do
things in a certain way.

00:10:47.981 --> 00:10:52.986 align:middle line:84%
And that expectation,
the emotional expectation

00:10:52.986 --> 00:10:57.031 align:middle line:84%
of the world being the
way it has always been,

00:10:57.031 --> 00:11:01.202 align:middle line:84%
translates into the
rhythm of our heart.

00:11:01.202 --> 00:11:04.831 align:middle line:84%
When we become rigid in our
thinking and our expectation,

00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:07.458 align:middle line:84%
our heartbeat
becomes more regular

00:11:07.458 --> 00:11:09.794 align:middle line:90%
and we lose the variability.

00:11:09.794 --> 00:11:12.755 align:middle line:84%
We lose our heart
rate variability.

00:11:12.755 --> 00:11:16.050 align:middle line:84%
And this is why change is
often hard for older people.

00:11:16.050 --> 00:11:19.053 align:middle line:90%
Not always, but it can be.

00:11:19.053 --> 00:11:22.765 align:middle line:84%
Tell you, one of the most
amazing examples of this for me

00:11:22.765 --> 00:11:25.018 align:middle line:90%
was my grandfather.

00:11:25.018 --> 00:11:27.854 align:middle line:84%
I was very close
to my grandfather.

00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:30.440 align:middle line:84%
My father left my family
when I was 10 years old.

00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:32.275 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know him very well.

00:11:32.275 --> 00:11:35.028 align:middle line:84%
And I became closer
to my grandfather

00:11:35.028 --> 00:11:37.447 align:middle line:84%
than I ever was to my father,
because I knew him longer,

00:11:37.447 --> 00:11:39.741 align:middle line:84%
and we shared
deeply, deep talks,

00:11:39.741 --> 00:11:41.451 align:middle line:84%
deep conversations
about the world

00:11:41.451 --> 00:11:43.620 align:middle line:90%
and the experiences of life.

00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:46.873 align:middle line:84%
And my grandfather lived
until he was 96 years old.

00:11:46.873 --> 00:11:48.790 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't with him
the moment that he

00:11:48.790 --> 00:11:52.962 align:middle line:84%
died during his 96th year,
but I was with him the week

00:11:52.962 --> 00:11:54.255 align:middle line:90%
that he passed.

00:11:54.255 --> 00:11:56.174 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know that
he was going to pass.

00:11:56.174 --> 00:11:58.217 align:middle line:90%
He seemed OK when I saw him.

00:11:58.217 --> 00:12:01.137 align:middle line:84%
But I had a sense, maybe
something was going on.

00:12:01.137 --> 00:12:01.930 align:middle line:90%
And I asked him.

00:12:01.930 --> 00:12:04.515 align:middle line:84%
I happened to ask him
on that last visit,

00:12:04.515 --> 00:12:06.768 align:middle line:84%
I said, grandpa,
you're 96 years old,

00:12:06.768 --> 00:12:10.647 align:middle line:84%
you've seen 96 years of
change in this world.

00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:11.689 align:middle line:90%
What has it meant to you?

00:12:11.689 --> 00:12:13.650 align:middle line:90%
What can you tell me?

00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:16.569 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at me with
this look that he always had.

00:12:16.569 --> 00:12:18.696 align:middle line:84%
And when he would smile,
his ears would wiggle.

00:12:18.696 --> 00:12:20.531 align:middle line:90%
I remember it.

00:12:20.531 --> 00:12:21.950 align:middle line:90%
And I miss that.

00:12:21.950 --> 00:12:25.119 align:middle line:84%
But what he said to me, smiled,
his ears wiggled a little bit,

00:12:25.119 --> 00:12:29.499 align:middle line:84%
and he said, Gregg, there was a
time when this world made sense

00:12:29.499 --> 00:12:30.500 align:middle line:90%
to me.

00:12:30.500 --> 00:12:33.461 align:middle line:84%
He said, there was a time
that I felt like I belonged.

00:12:33.461 --> 00:12:35.088 align:middle line:90%
I understood the world.

00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:37.465 align:middle line:90%
I understood how things worked.

00:12:37.465 --> 00:12:40.760 align:middle line:84%
I understood the people around
me and the way they think,

00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:44.639 align:middle line:84%
because they think the
way that I was thinking.

00:12:44.639 --> 00:12:46.432 align:middle line:84%
He said, but then
something changed.

00:12:46.432 --> 00:12:48.476 align:middle line:90%
Something began to happen.

00:12:48.476 --> 00:12:51.562 align:middle line:84%
And it was right around
the time of World War II.

00:12:51.562 --> 00:12:53.898 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't surprised
when I heard the timing,

00:12:53.898 --> 00:12:59.612 align:middle line:84%
because war typically
propels us with innovation

00:12:59.612 --> 00:13:01.656 align:middle line:84%
and new technology
and new discoveries

00:13:01.656 --> 00:13:03.199 align:middle line:84%
and new inventions
that quickly are

00:13:03.199 --> 00:13:05.410 align:middle line:90%
embraced by the general public.

00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:08.121 align:middle line:84%
And that's exactly what
happened in World War II.

00:13:08.121 --> 00:13:09.706 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden,
we had technology

00:13:09.706 --> 00:13:12.125 align:middle line:90%
we had never had before.

00:13:12.125 --> 00:13:16.421 align:middle line:84%
And my grandfather could never
keep up with that technology.

00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:19.090 align:middle line:84%
He couldn't understand,
for example, simple things.

00:13:19.090 --> 00:13:21.968 align:middle line:84%
He couldn't understand how
you put a piece of paper

00:13:21.968 --> 00:13:25.388 align:middle line:84%
into a fax machine in
an office in one city

00:13:25.388 --> 00:13:26.931 align:middle line:84%
and that piece of
paper comes out,

00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:28.725 align:middle line:84%
and all the information
is there on the fax

00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:29.392 align:middle line:90%
machine in another city.

00:13:29.392 --> 00:13:30.560 align:middle line:90%
It didn't make sense to him.

00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:33.813 align:middle line:84%
Because digital data
never made sense to him.

00:13:33.813 --> 00:13:35.440 align:middle line:90%
Lasers didn't make sense to him.

00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:38.109 align:middle line:84%
Coherent light waves
didn't make sense.

00:13:38.109 --> 00:13:40.862 align:middle line:84%
The way that jet planes
fly, in his lifetime,

00:13:40.862 --> 00:13:44.115 align:middle line:84%
he went from no
planes to jumbo jets,

00:13:44.115 --> 00:13:47.285 align:middle line:84%
and he could never understand
how something that big

00:13:47.285 --> 00:13:50.288 align:middle line:84%
could move in the air and
contain the fuel that it takes

00:13:50.288 --> 00:13:52.081 align:middle line:90%
to move fast enough to do that.

00:13:52.081 --> 00:13:54.459 align:middle line:90%
He said, I got lost.

00:13:54.459 --> 00:13:56.461 align:middle line:84%
He said, Gregg, I
got lost in my world.

00:13:56.461 --> 00:13:59.130 align:middle line:84%
He said, I'm no longer
a part of this world.

00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:01.549 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't make sense
to me any longer.

00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:04.844 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of that
week, my grandfather died.

00:14:04.844 --> 00:14:08.639 align:middle line:84%
And he died feeling like a
stranger in his own world.

00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:10.266 align:middle line:84%
And then maybe that
feeling contributed

00:14:10.266 --> 00:14:11.476 align:middle line:90%
to why he was no longer here.

00:14:11.476 --> 00:14:13.519 align:middle line:84%
He didn't have the
feeling and the connection

00:14:13.519 --> 00:14:16.022 align:middle line:84%
and the will to be
here any longer.

00:14:16.022 --> 00:14:18.191 align:middle line:84%
So I'm saying this to you,
because change was hard

00:14:18.191 --> 00:14:21.819 align:middle line:84%
for my grandfather, always
very hard for my grandfather.

00:14:21.819 --> 00:14:23.863 align:middle line:90%
He was so rigid in his thinking.

00:14:23.863 --> 00:14:27.366 align:middle line:84%
He wanted the world to be the
way it was before World War II,

00:14:27.366 --> 00:14:29.160 align:middle line:84%
before all those
changes happened.

00:14:29.160 --> 00:14:31.204 align:middle line:84%
And he used to
fight that change.

00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:33.331 align:middle line:84%
His heart rate
variability, no surprise,

00:14:33.331 --> 00:14:34.749 align:middle line:84%
when I went with
him to the doctor

00:14:34.749 --> 00:14:39.087 align:middle line:84%
and I would see that EKG,
his heart rate variability

00:14:39.087 --> 00:14:41.214 align:middle line:90%
looked like endless squiggles.

00:14:41.214 --> 00:14:44.884 align:middle line:84%
They weren't the big, deep
heart waves of someone

00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:48.221 align:middle line:84%
who's younger can embrace
the change in a healthy way.

00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:53.017 align:middle line:84%
It was the heartbeat of someone
who's lived to see a long life

00:14:53.017 --> 00:14:57.188 align:middle line:84%
and is struggling with accepting
and embracing the world

00:14:57.188 --> 00:14:59.524 align:middle line:84%
as it is now being
presented to him.

00:14:59.524 --> 00:15:01.359 align:middle line:90%
So heart rate variability.

00:15:01.359 --> 00:15:02.443 align:middle line:90%
How do we change that?

00:15:02.443 --> 00:15:03.778 align:middle line:90%
Well, the good news is you can.

00:15:03.778 --> 00:15:05.238 align:middle line:84%
You can change at
any time in life.

00:15:05.238 --> 00:15:08.032 align:middle line:84%
My grandfather,
if he had chosen,

00:15:08.032 --> 00:15:10.201 align:middle line:84%
could have embraced that
heart rate variability

00:15:10.201 --> 00:15:13.663 align:middle line:84%
in his life and the ability
to change his own heart

00:15:13.663 --> 00:15:14.622 align:middle line:90%
rate variability.

00:15:14.622 --> 00:15:16.749 align:middle line:90%
And how do you do that?

00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:20.503 align:middle line:84%
As I mentioned just a moment
ago, you already know how.

00:15:20.503 --> 00:15:22.839 align:middle line:10%
When we harmonize our
heart and our brain

00:15:22.839 --> 00:15:26.050 align:middle line:10%
together, when we shift our
awareness and know our heart,

00:15:26.050 --> 00:15:30.513 align:middle line:10%
number one, when we slow
our breathing to about five

00:15:30.513 --> 00:15:32.932 align:middle line:10%
seconds in, five
seconds out, and we

00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:35.351 align:middle line:10%
breathe as if that breath is
coming from our heart, number

00:15:35.351 --> 00:15:40.648 align:middle line:10%
two, and we begin to feel
the feelings of coherence,

00:15:40.648 --> 00:15:46.279 align:middle line:10%
the feelings of gratitude,
appreciation, compassion, care,

00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:49.991 align:middle line:10%
those kinds of feelings,
and we establish

00:15:49.991 --> 00:15:52.285 align:middle line:10%
the communication between
the heart and the brain--

00:15:52.285 --> 00:15:56.372 align:middle line:10%
0.1 Hertz is the talk between
