perfect sense.

00:18:51.505 --> 00:18:53.466 align:middle line:84%
Because the solar
cycles are also

00:18:53.466 --> 00:18:57.136 align:middle line:84%
based upon magnetic fields,
but they're on the sun.

00:18:57.136 --> 00:18:59.180 align:middle line:84%
When we talk about
sunspots, what

00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:01.182 align:middle line:84%
we see as sunspots
from the earth,

00:19:01.182 --> 00:19:04.852 align:middle line:84%
those spots are actually
magnetic fields on the sun.

00:19:04.852 --> 00:19:08.814 align:middle line:84%
The sun, our sun, does not
have a north and south pole,

00:19:08.814 --> 00:19:12.568 align:middle line:84%
like the Earth does, like Mars
and some of the other planets.

00:19:12.568 --> 00:19:15.988 align:middle line:84%
Our sun doesn't have a
single north and south pole.

00:19:15.988 --> 00:19:20.368 align:middle line:84%
What it has is many
north and south poles

00:19:20.368 --> 00:19:24.580 align:middle line:84%
that are specific to
each magnetic field,

00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:29.168 align:middle line:84%
or what we call magnetic storm
